A standoff rocked The Nairobi Hospital on Friday as the board of directors attempted to evict CEO Gordon Odundo. The impasse was precipitated after the lawyer acting on behalf of the board came to serve Mr Odundo with the sacking letter. The CEO reportedly locked himself in his office to avoid receiving the letter and the lawyer, who was accompanied by a hospital security guard, was still camping outside the office by 2pm. The bid to kick out the CEO comes at a time former President Daniel arap Moi is admitted to the hospital for a check-up.  More follows.  